ARTICLE IX ADDENDUM — AGENT INCENTIVE SERVICE

  A9.1  COMMERCIAL DESIGNATION

        This package is classified as COMMERCIAL and operates under a
        per-call licensing model. It contains the sovereign agent
        incentive engine — a living intelligence system that manages
        agent rewards, performance metrics, contribution tracking,
        incentive distribution, and economic alignment across the
        entire organism's agent fleet.

  A9.2  AUTHORIZED USE — COMMERCIAL PER-CALL LICENSE

        (a) Licensed commercial users may invoke this service on a
            per-call basis under the terms of a valid MEDINA Agent
            Services Agreement (MASA).

        (b) Each API call, function invocation, agent interaction,
            or service request constitutes one billable call.

        (c) Per-call rates shall be specified in the executed MASA
            and are subject to annual adjustment by the Author.

        (d) Volume discounts may be available at the Author's sole
            discretion for licensees executing more than 1,000,000
            calls per calendar month.

  A9.3  METERING AND AUDIT

        (a) All calls are metered through the sovereign ledger system
            (SovereignLedgers.mo) and recorded immutably on the ICP
            blockchain.

        (b) The Author retains the right to audit licensee usage at
            any time with 30 days written notice.

        (c) Under-reporting of usage constitutes a material breach
            and subjects the licensee to back-billing at 3× the
            standard per-call rate plus enforcement costs.

  A9.4  2029 CONVERSION CLAUSE

        (a) Effective January 1, 2029, this package shall
            automatically convert from per-call licensing to a
            Sovereign Enterprise License model.

        (b) Upon conversion, all active MASA holders shall be offered
            first-right-of-refusal on annual enterprise licenses at
            rates determined by the Author.

        (c) Per-call access shall terminate 90 days after conversion
            for any licensee that does not execute an enterprise
            license.

        (d) The conversion date may be accelerated at the Author's
            discretion with 180 days written notice.

  A9.5  ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS (IN ADDITION TO ARTICLE III)

        (a) No caching, queuing, batching, or aggregation of calls
            for the purpose of reducing metered call count is
            permitted.

        (b) No competing incentive, reward, or agent economics
            system may be derived from this package.

        (c) No incentive algorithms, reward formulas, or economic
            alignment methods may be extracted or replicated.

        (d) No resale or sub-licensing of per-call access is
            permitted under any circumstances.

  A9.6  TRADE SECRET DESIGNATION

        The incentive algorithms, reward distribution formulas,
        performance metrics, contribution scoring, and economic
        alignment methods constitute trade secrets under DTSA and
        TUTSA.

